I. Structural Foundation and Objectives

1. Rationale and Nature

This is a cash-flow-based securitisation-style funding for vehicle inventory purchases and sales (short-term, self-liquidating assets).
The true sale concept is replaced by a secured loan structure, where the SPV funds Auto1â€™s CarCo against pledged inventory and related receivables.
Purpose: flexible revolving liquidity to finance working capital (purchase/refurbishment of vehicles).

2. Structure and Instruments
	â€¢	Three-tier funding stack:
	â€¢	Senior Notes / Senior Loan (AAA/A-rated): External investors.
	â€¢	Mezzanine Notes / Loan (BB-rated): Partly internal (Auto1 Group Operations SE).
	â€¢	Junior Loan / Notes: Fully retained, providing first-loss buffer.
	â€¢	Issuer funding chain: Senior and mezzanine investors lend to the Issuer â†’ Issuer on-lends to CarCo â†’ CarCo funds inventory.

3. Amendment Purpose (2025)
	â€¢	Carve-out of Italian assets (migrated to a standalone compartment structure).
	â€¢	Reduction of total senior commitments (reflecting deleveraging and geographic focus).
	â€¢	Operational audit enhancement â€“ increasing testing thresholds for reconciliation and eligibility verification.
	â€¢	Alignment with rating conditions: Senior Notes require reaffirmed A(sf) from S&P and Scope.

