â¸»

ğŸ“ˆ 6ï¸âƒ£ How to present it as a sign of robustness

You can spin this in your portfolio performance or credit memo as a proof of structural resilience:

â€œEven in months where available CarCo collections were temporarily below expected levels, the deficiency retention mechanism ensured cash was trapped and preserved for senior creditors. The Issuer continued to service note obligations on time through available reserves and accumulated OC, with no investor payment delays.â€

Add a Deficiency Coverage Ratio to illustrate this:

Deficiency_Coverage_% = (Liquidity_Reserve + Available_Issuer_Cash) / Deficiency_Amount

